        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hi,\r\n\r\ntrying this call (using gettext adapter)\r\n\r\nbq. $translate->plural('Software','Software',2);\r\n\r\nnever give me the plural or singular translation of the term but only Software.\r\n\r\nIs it a limitation of Zend_Translate or a bug ?\r\nWithout it, complete translations are quite difficult.\r\n\r\nCalling \r\nbq. $translate->plural('Software','Softwares',2); \r\nis not correct because Software have no plural forms.\r\n\r\nRegards\r\n\r\nPS : \r\n\r\npo file content : \r\n{quote}\r\nmsgid \"Software\"\r\nmsgid_plural \"Software\"\r\nmsgstr[0] \"Logiciel\"\r\nmsgstr[1] \"Logiciels\"\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nprint_r($this->_data); at the end of the Zend_Translate_Adapter_Gettext::_loadTranslationData function \r\n{quote}\r\nArray ( [fr_FR] => Array ( [Software] => ) )\r\n{quote}\r\n"
        },
